<subSubSection pageNumber="446" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="446">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="446">Note:</emphasis>
Smith incorrectly described the Martyn plate as a 
<typeStatus>neotype</typeStatus>
. However, as it was an original element for the name, this is a valid typification under Art. 9.8, despite the fact that some later authors (e.g. Reveal in Jarvis &amp; al., 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="446">Regnum Veg.</emphasis>
127: 37. 1993; Hind in Bosser &amp; al., 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="446">Fl. Mascareignes</emphasis>
109: 196. 1993) have indicated a Clifford sheet as the 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
